richText.content: Covid-19 Golf Protocols

Booking / Ordering Process

  • Download the Taboo App
  • Tee Times must be paid in advance through our website or Taboo App. There are no monetary refunds, a credit will be given towards a future round. No walk-up tee times will be allowed.
  • Tee time intervals are 8 minutes.
  • All Food and Beverage orders will be take-out only, and ordered online through the Taboo App.
  • Hours of Operation for the Proshop and Food and Beverage are 7:00am to 7:00pm daily.
  • Last Food and Beverage order of the day must be placed by 6:45pm.
  • Rental clubs are now available. Feeâ€™s will apply.

Arrival

  • Guests may only arrive up to 40 minutes before tee time and must complete the COVID-19 Self Declaration Form prior to arrival.
  • Social Distancing â€“ While on property, always allow for a minimum of 6ft between individuals. Signage will be installed throughout the property to help you maintain a safe distance between you and other guests.
  • Limited number of guests will be allowed in the Pro Shop at one time. Please follow all directional signage when entering the Pro Shop.
  • Guests MUST wear face protection while inside the Pro Shop.
  • The Pro Shop & on course washrooms will be open.
  • Bag drop is not available; please load your bag onto your cart. All players will be required to handle their own clubs from arrival to departure.
  • Singles and twosomes will be paired up to create foursomes.
  • NO outside alcohol is permitted on property, including the parking lot. Individuals failing to abide by this policy will be asked to leave the property immediately.

On Course

  • The Driving Range and Practice facility are open. Only 3 groups, or maximum 12 players allowed at a time. You will be invited to use the practice facility only 30 minutes prior to your scheduled tee time.
  • Scorecards will be available on your carts, scorecard is also available virtually â€“ please download and use the Taboo App.
  • Two Guests while on carts who are not members of the same household must wear a mask. If you wish to utilize a divider you are free to do so, but that does not supersede the requirement for 2 members of different households riding in a cart together from having to wear a mask.

Golf Cart Usage

  • I agree to assume all risks and loss or damage to golf carts rented or borrowed from the Taboo Golf Course.
  • I agree to assume the risk of injury to the Operator or other individuals and damage to other property arising from the use of the golf cart.
  • I agree to waive any and all claims against the Taboo Golf Club, Taboo Muskoka and It's employees from any and all liability for any loss, damage, expense or injury, including death, that I may suffer as a result of golfing, the use of a rented or borrowed golf cart or due to any cause whatsoever.
